definition: can/to be possible/to be able to/will/to be likely to/to be sure to/to assemble/to meet/to gather/to see/union/group/association/CL:個|个[ge4]/a moment (Taiwan pr. for this sense is [hui3])

sentences.english: Become active in a professional association. This means doing more than paying dues and showing up for meetings.
sentences.chinese: 这就意味着，不再只是交交会费，出席一下会议。

sentences.english: Proposals were to establish a sliding scale of fess, based on the annual budget of associations.
sentences.chinese: 会议提议，基于协会的年度预算而建立一套会费机制。

sentences.english: Consider all fees associated with each group.
sentences.chinese: 将每个社团的入会费综合起来考虑。

sentences.english: All members shall pay in time their membership fee so as to retain their membership.
sentences.chinese: 所有会员必须每年准时缴交指定之会费以确保其会籍。

sentences.english: They kept back 80 dollars from my wages for trade union membership dues.
sentences.chinese: 他们从我的工资中扣下80元钱交工会会费。

sentences.english: He went round the various offices to collect the dues.
sentences.chinese: 他到各个办公室去收会费。

sentences.english: Membersip fees should be paid within the first quarter of every year.
sentences.chinese: 每年第一个季度内须交齐当年会费。

sentences.english: One-time Ordinary Membership Fee is HKD10 only.
sentences.chinese: 普通会员一次性入会费用为港币拾圆正。

sentences.english: Attached with a crossed cheque amount of HKD200.00, as for the renewal fee of HKKKA membership.
sentences.chinese: 之划线支票，以作本会新一年度之续会会费。

sentences.english: They have initiation fees and monthly minimums, all within the means of this target segment.
sentences.chinese: 通常的收费方式是入会费和每月的最低消费相结合。

sentences.english: The exact amount that Floey will have to pay, will be decided when the two teams meet next time.
sentences.chinese: “转会费”的准确数目将在两队下次相遇时确定。

sentences.english: That remains the highest transfer fee ever paid for a player.
sentences.chinese: 这笔金额直到现在仍然是支付球员转会费最高的一笔。

sentences.english: Right-to-work laws say that workers don't have to join unions or pay union dues.
sentences.chinese: 工作权利法认为工人们没有加入工会或支付会费。

sentences.english: A monthly subscription costs about the same as one restaurant meal in London.
sentences.chinese: 俱乐部每月会费仅相当于在伦敦餐馆吃一顿饭的成本。

sentences.english: They were chucked out of the club for failing to pay the membership dues.
sentences.chinese: 他们由于不缴纳会费而被俱乐部除名。

definition: to join a society, association etc
to hand in/to hand over/to seize
to pay up/to shell out/to hand over the money to cover sth
